t the software company for other uses see intuit disambiguation intuit inc the intuit headquarters in mountain view type public traded as nasdaq intu nasdaq component sp  component industry enterprise software founded   years ago  palo alto california us founder scott cook tom proulx headquarters mountain view california us key people brad smith chairman and ceo products personal finance accounting and tax return software revenue us billion  operating income us billion  net income us million  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  number of employees   website wwwintuitcom intuit inc is a business and financial software company that develops and sells financial accounting and tax preparation software and related services for small businesses accountants and individuals the company is headquartered in mountain view california greater than  of its revenues and earnings come from its activities within the united states intuit produces turbotax a consumer tax preparation application the small business accounting program quickbooks professional tax solutions proseries and lacerte and multiple payroll products in april  intuit completed the sale of its original flagship product quicken to hig capital in addition to the united states the company has offices in seven countries around the world uk australia france singapore india brazil and canada contents  history  online communities  acquisitions and carveouts  controversies and lobbying  allegations of willfully allowing fraudulent returns  lawsuits  see also  references  external links historyedit the company was founded in  by scott cook and tom proulx in palo alto california intuit was conceived by scott cook whose prior work at procter  gamble helped him realize that personal computers would lend themselves towards replacements for paperandpencil based personal accounting on his quest to find a programmer he ended up running into tom proulx at stanford the two started intuit which initially operated out of a modest room on university avenue in palo alto the first version of quicken was coded in microsofts basic programming language for the ibm pc and ucsd pascal for the apple ii by tom proulx and had to contend with a dozen serious competitors in  microsoft decided to produce a competitor to quicken called microsoft money to win retailers loyalty intuit included a us rebate coupon redeemable on software customers purchased in their stores this was the first time a software company offered a rebate roughly around the same time the company engaged john doerr of kleiner perkins caufield  byers and diversified its product lineup in  intuit went public and used the proceeds to make a key acquisition the taxpreparation software company chipsoft based in san diego the time after the ipo was marked by rapid growth and culminated with a buyout offer from microsoft in  at this time intuits market capitalization reached us billion when the buyout fell through because of the united states department of justices disapproval the company came under intense pressure in the late s when microsoft started to compete vigorously with its core quicken business in response intuit launched new webbased products and solutions and put more emphasis on quickbooks and on turbotax the company made a number of investments around this time among others it purchased a large stake in excite and acquired lacerte software a dallasbased developer of tax preparation software used by tax professionals it also divested itself of its online bill payment service unit and extended and strengthened its partnership with checkfree today intuit has more than us billion in annual revenue and a market capitalization of more than us billioncitation needed intuit was ranked in fortunes top  best companies to work for in  intuit was ranked in fortunes americas most admired software companies in  in june  intuit announced it would sell its financial services unit to private equity firm thoma bravo for  billion in june 